That spans the language fundamentals, the shell-specific mechanics, the Unix text-processing toolkit, error handling, and the DevOps-flavored automation patterns. For day-to-day work, the highest-leverage skills are solid Bash (with set -euo pipefail, parameter expansion, and trap), the grep/sed/awk/jq toolkit, and Python for anything beyond ~50 lines of glue.